reviews.text:
A hot-pot restaurant providing All-you-can-eat in 90 minutes at difference prices and choices of additional foods (with charge) on top. Meats, vegetables and other foods were fresh.
Spacious between tables facilitating walking to & fro between food bar and table.
The merit is sitting next to the window wall looking downstairs watching people browsing and riding up & down on the escalators while the clouds moving on the artificial blue sky above.
A good place!
I chose the $278 per pax for dinner. Food is OK, not super wow. Soup is nothing special.
This restaurant supports the Hong Kong gang police who wants to murder protesters.

Good value all you can eat hotpot on your own mini stove. Unlimited supply of beef, chicken, pork, veggies, noodles, and tasty sauces, and self-served yogart ice cream tap all to your hearts content for just about HK$120. Lunch session begins at 12 noon with no time limit (till 3pm) between Mon. & Thur. The only complaint is fruit flies are a bit out of control.

result.name: 日牛涮涮鍋專門店

reviews.text:
入座安排混亂，即使有4人位，都要拆開比排我更後的客人入座。
職員態度惡劣，上前向他查詢，竟同我説等不了就不好吃。
店員話得閒遊行就唔好去佢度食去其他地方食喎，咁好嘅服務緊係要好好支持

食物唔新鮮，有毛
員工態度差，叫更換也不情不願
不敢再來了

牛肉很新鮮，即使是最平的牛肉，也很嫩滑，不過第二輪以後的牛肉會比第一輪的差。
外面的蔬菜選擇也不少，可惜的是醬汁卻沒有蒜蓉和小辣椒。
湯底我們選擇一個昆布鍋和一個壽喜燒鍋，壽喜燒鵝真的很好吃，牛肉點一些蛋漿，提升很多。
有一段小插曲就是餐廳裏有小麻雀，感覺有點不衛生，不過現在不是禽流感期，所以還好。
最後配上一個乳酪作甜品，令整頓飯都很滿足。
日牛涮涮鍋是眾多日式打邊爐選擇其中一個比較價格相宜的，特別是下午茶時段比較少人，不用排隊，店員服務也不錯食物，上菜速度快，值得推介。
